President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Alabama due to the impact of Tropical Storm Ida. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas, specifically Baldwin and Mobile Counties. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Michael Bolch has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-4600.